 @dr.bunterhidenbrobruh5502  yeah he was never a good live performer. But on the albums he managed to sound incredible
I don't think it's easy to do metal vocals night after night on tour. You literally have to have opera singer training, in order to protect your voice enough to do well, and absolutely no drinking allowed. But yeah, the best live metal singers quite literally go through opera singer training, learning all the warmups, all the exercises, that they have to do each and every day before and after every performance in order to protect their voice and be able to do low growls and high pitched screams etc and not just immediately lose their voice on the first night from doing that. Some metal bands do actually do this training, but it's rare.
I know the singer of the band Enter Shikari does this training and these warm up exercises, cos they're from the same town as the one I grew up in, so I've got a fair few friends who are friends with the band themselves (at least before they got big anyway). And they all tell me the singer does these exercises. It's a good idea but most metal singers would probably think it goes against the spirit of metal or some bollocks like that. Like, try and convince Ozzy Osborne to quit drugs and drinking and bat-head eating and start training to be an opera singer, he probably won't take it well.

