 @tugra_us  That's exactly why I'm okay with the Pantera tribute tour with Zakk: Mr. Jerry Abbott deserves to see, at least one last time, that those sons he gave to the world, who gave their lives to the music, created music so timeless and incomparable that it still resonates with so many of us today.

Pantera were the fathers of metal as we know it today, which makes Mr. Jerry Abbott the grandfather of metal as we know it today.  Without his parentage and influence and unwavering support, there would have been no Dime & Vinnie, and there would have been no Pantera. We can argue and debate about the legitimacy of the upcoming tribute tour all we want, but one thing we should all agree on is that we owe that man every last ounce of love that we have for Dime & Vinnie and Pantera.

